### Gold museum

The Gold Museum of the Bank of the Republic of Colombia is an institution open to the public whose purpose is the acquisition, conservation and exhibition of pieces of goldsmithing and pottery of indigenous cultures of the pre-Columbian period of present-day Colombia. It is located on the corner of Calle 16 with Carrera 5, has more than 34,000 pieces made of gold, 20,000 lithic objects, ceramics, precious stones, and textiles belonging to the Quimbaya, Calima, Tayrona, Zenú, Muisca, Tolima cultures , Tumaco and Magdalena among others.
