### Colpatria Tower

The Colpatria Tower is a skyscraper located in Bogotá, in the northern part of the Las Nieves neighborhood. Its commercial area constitutes an extension of the International Center of the city. With its 50 floors, it is the second tallest building in the city as well as one of its icons. It was completed in 1979 and has a height of 196 meters. In it are the offices of various companies, among which are the companies of the Colpatria Group, owner of the tower.
 
On its roof there is a viewpoint to appreciate much of the city and the savannah of Bogotá. In 1998, thirty-six xenon lights were installed, which at the end of 2012 were replaced with LED technology lights.
